Use `ConfigureLifecycleEvents` in `MauiProgram.cs`:

```csharp
builder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
{
#if ANDROID
    events.AddAndroid(android => android
        .OnPause(activity =>
        {
            // App losing focus (partially visible)
        })
        .OnStop(activity =>
        {
            // App fully backgrounded
        }));
#elif IOS || MACCATALYST
    events.AddiOS(ios => ios
        .DidEnterBackground(app =>
        {
            // App entered background
        }));
#endif
});
```

**Or use cross-platform Window events** if you don't need native-level granularity — `Stopped` maps to Android `OnStop` and iOS `DidEnterBackground`:

```csharp
// In App.xaml.cs
protected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)
{
    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);
    window.Stopped += (s, e) => { /* save state here */ };
    return window;
}
```

**Key notes:**
- `Deactivated` ≠ `Stopped` — a notification shade triggers Deactivated without Stopped.
- On Android, the back button can skip `Stopped` and go straight to `Destroying`, so save critical state in both.
- Keep handlers fast (<2s) to avoid ANR on Android or watchdog kills on iOS.
